 </p>
 <p>
  <span class="eq">
   <var>
    <span class="vec">⃗</span>
    c
   </var>
   =
   <b>hp</b>
   (
   <span class="b0">[</span>
   10; 11; 12; 13
   <span class="b0">]</span>
   )  =
   <b class="b0">[</b>
   10 11 12 13
   <b class="b0">]</b>
  </span>
 </p>
 <p>
  <span class="eq">
   <b>
    <var>D</var>
   </b>
   =
   <b>augment</b>
   (
   <b>
    <var>A</var>
   </b>
   ;
   <b>
    <var>B</var>
   </b>
   ;
   <var>
    <span class="vec">⃗</span>
    c
   </var>
   )  =
   <span class="matrix">
    <span class="tr">
     <span class="td">
     </span>
     <span class="td">1</span>
     <span class="td">2</span>
     <span class="td">1</span>
     <span class="td">2</span>
     <span class="td">3</span>
     <span class="td">10</span>
     <span class="td">
     </span>
    </span>
    <span class="tr">
     <span class="td">
     </span>
     <span class="td">3</span>
     <span class="td">4</span>
     <span class="td">4</span>
     <span class="td">5</span>
     <span class="td">6</span>
     <span class="td">11</span>
     <span class="td">
     </span>
    </span>
    <span class="tr">
     <span class="td">
     </span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">7</span>
     <span class="td">8</span>
     <span class="td">9</span>
     <span class="td">12</span>
     <span class="td">
     </span>
    </span>
    <span class="tr">
     <span class="td">
     </span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">13</span>
     <span class="td">
     </span>
    </span>
   </span>
  </span>
  - creates a general rectangular matrix by joining the input matrices side to side
 </p>
 <p>
  <span class="eq">
